main event: Multiple sightings of unidentified flying objects reported in New Carlisle, Ohio during September 1966.
interesting points: The sightings involved two objects on September 2, observed for 5 minutes, and one object on September 4, observed for 9 seconds., Ground visual observations were the primary method of sighting., Citizens and military personnel reported sightings, indicating varied sources., The reports concluded with insufficient data for evaluation., No photographs were included in the reports.
witness description: A civilian and a military personnel provided reports.
